HEADWORD: Schwenkfeldian
<hw>Schwenk"feld`i*an</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A member of a religious sect
founded by Kaspar von Schwenkfeld, a Silesian reformer who disagreed
with Luther, especially on the deification of the body of
Christ.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

